                <head>345. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>British Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Anthony Eden</persName> and
                    Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_LS1">Selwyn Lloyd</persName> visited
                    Washington January 30–February 1 for talks with President <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>, Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>, and other U.S. officials. Regarding the
                        <persName corresp="#p_ESA1">Eden</persName> talks, including material
                    relating to Iran, see <ref target="#d94">Documents 94</ref> ff.</p>
            </div>
